SIMPLE: snicker
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snicker
<hw>Snick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Snickered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Snickering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>snikken</ets> to sob, to sigh.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>snigger</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To laugh slyly; to laugh
in one's sleeve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To laugh with audible catches of voice, as when
persons attempt to suppress loud laughter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snicker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snicker
<hw>Snick"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A half suppressed, broken
laugh.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>snigger</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snide</ent>⟦br⟧
